    "updated_at": "2013-09-04T05:41:08Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yeah, I'm all for a `-j` flag going forward, it was just going to make this code a lot uglier on the parser side of things, as @takluyver pointed out. In the meantime, the `--fast` flag works eponymously, and can later be an alias for just `-j` when the number of threads is specified. I added that it closes #1880 to the PR description, so GH can do it's magic in auto-closing that when this lands\n"
